00:22:31,240 --> 00:22:32,720
But if they try to hit us back,

270
00:22:33,759 --> 00:22:35,279
we'll keep the ECUs.

271
00:22:35,839 --> 00:22:37,960
Their cars will only ever be scrap metal.

272
00:22:38,039 --> 00:22:38,880
Good, right?

273
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:52,000
Oops.

274
00:22:53,160 --> 00:22:54,279
I'm sorry.

275
00:22:54,880 --> 00:22:56,319
Don't mind me. I'm done here.

276
00:23:00,480 --> 00:23:03,839
Prom didn't mean to cause trouble
for our family, you know?

277
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:05,480
Please don't take offense.

278
00:23:06,119 --> 00:23:10,599
If you feel
that Prom has any room for improvement

279
00:23:11,400 --> 00:23:14,559
and you'd like to teach him
how to be a better man,

280
00:23:15,119 --> 00:23:16,319
I would welcome that.

281
00:23:18,839 --> 00:23:20,200
Besides,

282
00:23:20,920 --> 00:23:23,519
we are both single parents,

283
00:23:23,599 --> 00:23:27,920
so wouldn't it be better
if we worked together to be his parents?

284
00:23:30,799 --> 00:23:35,160
You should look after your own kids.
Khim causes enough trouble for me.

285
00:23:35,799 --> 00:23:36,640
Excuse me.

286
00:23:38,519 --> 00:23:39,359
Dad?

287
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,640
It's good that you're here.

288
00:23:44,359 --> 00:23:45,759
I need to talk to you.

289
00:23:49,799 --> 00:23:50,880
Oops.

290
00:23:51,759 --> 00:23:52,799
Sorry, sweetie.

291
00:23:53,319 --> 00:23:56,039
I didn't expect to see you here.

292
00:24:16,279 --> 00:24:18,119
I'm a big girl now.

293
00:24:19,920 --> 00:24:22,160
I would understand
if you were seeing someone.

294
00:24:23,839 --> 00:24:25,519
You don't have to hide her from me.

295
00:24:25,599 --> 00:24:26,920
I'm not a little girl.

296
00:24:29,079 --> 00:24:30,599
You've been around the block now.

297
00:24:31,960 --> 00:24:33,160
Nothing can shock you now.

298
00:24:42,640 --> 00:24:43,880
Gaogla

299
00:24:44,559 --> 00:24:46,440
has gave the check back.

300
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:49,960
Maybe he never planned to blackmail me.

301
00:24:50,039 --> 00:24:51,880
You tried to buy him off.

302
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:54,279
You disrespected both him and me.

303
00:24:55,440 --> 00:24:56,519
Don't you understand?

304
00:24:57,759 --> 00:24:59,160
He gave the check back

305
00:24:59,240 --> 00:25:03,079
to make himself look like a gentleman.
You still can't see that?

306
00:25:04,039 --> 00:25:07,720
I'm not so boy crazy
that I can't tell right from wrong.

307
00:25:16,200 --> 00:25:18,279
Every problem I've caused,

308
00:25:19,480 --> 00:25:21,960
I'm ready to take responsibility
for them myself.

309
00:25:24,400 --> 00:25:27,640
I'll never bring shame on you again.

310
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:29,519
I promise.

311
00:25:50,400 --> 00:25:51,759
PAY MR. GAOGLA CHAYODOM

312
00:25:57,359 --> 00:25:58,319
Gaogla.

313
00:26:02,519 --> 00:26:03,680
Gaogla.

314
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:56,279
Auntie Oonruean?

315
00:26:56,920 --> 00:26:58,039
It's me.

316
00:27:03,799 --> 00:27:07,000
-What is it?
-I need your help with something.

317
00:27:08,440 --> 00:27:11,599
A magazine wants to do
a photo shoot with me and Tan.

318
00:27:11,680 --> 00:27:14,000
But Tan refuses to do it.

319
00:27:14,839 --> 00:27:17,160
Can you ask him what he's so afraid of?

320
00:27:18,480 --> 00:27:21,160
I guess Tan has his own reasons.

321
00:27:22,359 --> 00:27:24,039
Are you refusing to ask him

322
00:27:24,119 --> 00:27:26,799
because… you're jealous?

323
00:27:26,880 --> 00:27:29,039
You want to keep him
as a friend with benefits?

324
00:27:30,000 --> 00:27:31,960
Tan and I aren't dating each other.

325
00:27:32,960 --> 00:27:37,200
So I guess if I started dating Tan,
you'd be okay with that?

326
00:27:38,359 --> 00:27:39,400
Of course that's okay.

327
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:42,680
That's great to hear.

328
00:27:43,680 --> 00:27:46,240
Now I can tell Tan not to worry about it

329
00:27:46,319 --> 00:27:48,920
because you gave us your blessing.

330
00:27:55,279 --> 00:27:56,119
Miss Khim?

331
00:27:56,839 --> 00:27:58,200
Hello, Miss Khim?

332
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:00,839
Yes?

333
00:28:10,839 --> 00:28:14,480
It's nice to have a heart-to-heart
as cousins once in a while, isn't it?

334
00:28:17,880 --> 00:28:19,359
I've set the table, miss.

335
00:28:19,880 --> 00:28:21,079
Your father is waiting.0

336
00:28:21,680 --> 00:28:24,599
When you're the only daughter,
your dad watches you like a hawk.

337
00:28:25,359 --> 00:28:26,599
He watches your every move.

338
00:28:27,680 --> 00:28:29,960
You should go. Don't keep him waiting.

339
00:28:30,039 --> 00:28:30,880
Yes, Auntie Oon.

340
00:28:38,599 --> 00:28:40,839
She has spread her wings out there.

341
00:28:40,920 --> 00:28:43,119
She won't be put back
in her gilded cage again.

342
00:28:44,160 --> 00:28:45,279
Reset your expectations.

343
00:28:45,880 --> 00:28:47,240
She is disobedient.

344
00:28:48,279 --> 00:28:49,559
You can't call her back.

345
00:28:58,359 --> 00:29:02,079
Did I keep you waiting?
Sorry I'm just a bit late.

346
00:29:04,880 --> 00:29:06,880
I'll see a hotel group
in New York next week.

347
00:29:08,079 --> 00:29:09,519
What about me, Uncle?

348
00:29:09,599 --> 00:29:11,640
Stay here and deal with your car.

349
00:29:15,559 --> 00:29:17,279
Your classes resume next month, right?

350
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:23,440
Is it such a good idea to have her
studying somewhere so far away?

351
00:29:24,119 --> 00:29:24,960
Why do you ask?

352
00:29:25,559 --> 00:29:27,319
She's in a Top Five university.

353
00:29:27,400 --> 00:29:28,799
She can't throw that away.

354
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:32,559
But I don't want to go back yet.

355
00:29:34,119 --> 00:29:35,880
You've been home for over a month.

356
00:29:35,960 --> 00:29:37,480
Maybe studying is not a priority.

357
00:29:38,200 --> 00:29:39,720
Studying is so stressful.

358
00:29:39,799 --> 00:29:41,359
Maybe if you find a…

359
00:29:41,440 --> 00:29:43,000
…that would be better.

360
00:29:44,559 --> 00:29:46,000
She's not like you, Prim.

361
00:29:46,079 --> 00:29:47,720
Come on, Prom.

362
00:29:47,799 --> 00:29:51,359
I'm not stupid enough to debase myself
by letting any random man have me.

363
00:29:55,759 --> 00:29:57,200
Return to England immediately.

364
00:29:57,720 --> 00:29:58,640
End of discussion.

365
00:30:07,079 --> 00:30:07,920
Pregnant?

366
00:30:08,440 --> 00:30:12,519
Well, I saw the pregnancy test in her room
with my very own eyes.

367
00:30:13,119 --> 00:30:15,759
Uncle Seen is too biased towards her
to see the ugly truth.

368
00:30:15,839 --> 00:30:19,200
He probably doesn't know
what a degenerate she has become.

369
00:30:20,400 --> 00:30:25,039
I should've embarrassed them more
so he'd stop looking down on me.

370
00:30:26,880 --> 00:30:27,960
If she's pregnant,

371
00:30:28,519 --> 00:30:30,759
how can she cope
with going back to university?

372
00:30:31,880 --> 00:30:34,240
Mom, this isn't something
you can just hide.

373
00:30:35,160 --> 00:30:38,799
And who can tell
if her dear old Auntie Oonruean

374
00:30:38,880 --> 00:30:40,400
knows and is protecting her?

375
00:30:41,960 --> 00:30:44,799
I think if she knew,
she'd help her hide it.

376
00:30:45,519 --> 00:30:48,440
Maybe she'd even take advantage
of Seen's absences

377
00:30:49,039 --> 00:30:51,559
to dispose of all the evidence.

378
00:30:51,640 --> 00:30:54,680
We can't let all this
just go away quietly.

379
00:30:54,759 --> 00:30:56,559
This shock could kill Uncle Seen.

380
00:30:57,160 --> 00:30:59,359
Now his own daughter is
such a delinquent,

381
00:30:59,440 --> 00:31:03,039
let's see if Uncle Seen
would dare to look down on me anymore.

382
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:09,519
Return to England immediately.

383
00:31:10,079 --> 00:31:11,079
End of discussion.

384
00:31:42,319 --> 00:31:43,519
If we trust each other,

385
00:31:44,720 --> 00:31:45,640
it won't be so hard.

386
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:48,119
Trust me with your life.

387
00:32:01,960 --> 00:32:02,799
Hey, Khem,

388
00:32:03,359 --> 00:32:04,319
pass me the wrench.

389
00:32:09,039 --> 00:32:10,119
I asked for the wrench,

390
00:32:10,640 --> 00:32:11,640
not the screwdriver.

391
00:32:21,279 --> 00:32:22,599
What are you doing, Khem?

392
00:32:32,519 --> 00:32:33,680
When you said…

393
00:32:35,519 --> 00:32:36,960
"If we trust each other,

394
00:32:37,640 --> 00:32:38,720
it won't be so hard."

395
00:32:40,519 --> 00:32:42,440
"Trust me with your life,"

396
00:32:43,559 --> 00:32:45,000
did you mean that,

397
00:32:45,519 --> 00:32:48,880
or was it just something cool to say?

398
00:32:58,240 --> 00:33:01,240
I'm a man of my word. I meant what I said.

399
00:33:06,200 --> 00:33:09,079
I gave the check back to my dad.

400
00:33:10,680 --> 00:33:14,400
Why did you run away?
You should have stayed to talk.

401
00:33:14,480 --> 00:33:18,000
Well, you said you wanted to end it.
You didn't want me to come see you.

402
00:33:19,720 --> 00:33:21,519
Let's end things here.

403
00:33:21,599 --> 00:33:23,640
It's not worth it for either of us.

404
00:33:23,720 --> 00:33:25,960
Just pretend that we've never met.

405
00:33:27,119 --> 00:33:28,640
Let's not ruin our lives more.

406
00:33:30,799 --> 00:33:31,680
Actually,

407
00:33:32,839 --> 00:33:34,599
we're virtually strangers.

408
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:46,359
Tie them properly, or you'll trip.

409
00:33:49,119 --> 00:33:51,799
If you're going to be so nice to me,

410
00:33:51,880 --> 00:33:54,279
I could cause more trouble for you.

411
00:34:06,039 --> 00:34:07,480
Would you be mad at me

412
00:34:08,679 --> 00:34:10,400
if I told you…

413
00:34:14,280 --> 00:34:15,679
that I'm pregnant?

414
00:34:15,760 --> 00:34:16,599
What?

415
00:34:28,119 --> 00:34:29,159
You're pregnant?

416
00:34:33,639 --> 00:34:35,800
Do you… do you think I'm lying?

417
00:34:35,880 --> 00:34:36,719
No.

418
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:41,280
I knew it would turn out like this.

419
00:34:42,519 --> 00:34:44,159
I shouldn't have told you.

420
00:34:45,960 --> 00:34:48,440
Wait. Hey.

421
00:34:50,199 --> 00:34:51,159
Come on. Wait.

422
00:34:57,239 --> 00:34:58,880
Are you very mad at me?

423
00:34:59,400 --> 00:35:00,960
Mad at you? For what?

424
00:35:01,559 --> 00:35:03,159
I should apologize to you.

425
00:35:04,119 --> 00:35:07,320
Actually, you can insult me,
or slap me, or whatever you want.

426
00:35:07,400 --> 00:35:09,679
Come on, slap me really hard. Go on.

427
00:35:11,639 --> 00:35:12,480
No.

428
00:35:14,119 --> 00:35:15,360
It wasn't your fault.

429
00:35:16,960 --> 00:35:20,559
I have to go back to university.

430
00:35:23,320 --> 00:35:27,519
I can't let… this incident derail my life.

431
00:35:43,760 --> 00:35:44,599
You mean

432
00:35:45,599 --> 00:35:47,119
you're not keeping the baby?

433
00:35:53,519 --> 00:35:54,880
If we don't do this,

434
00:35:56,039 --> 00:35:58,760
my dad could kill me or you.

435
00:36:02,679 --> 00:36:04,199
We'll eliminate the problem.

436
00:36:04,280 --> 00:36:06,639
We can't let anyone else
suffer because of us.

437
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:10,559
This may be the only way.

438
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:18,519
Can you please tell me

439
00:36:19,199 --> 00:36:20,920
how I should begin?

440
00:36:25,239 --> 00:36:26,719
Begin by trusting each other,

441
00:36:27,960 --> 00:36:29,440
and we can get through anything.

442
00:36:59,320 --> 00:37:00,639
Are you leaving now?

443
00:37:01,480 --> 00:37:02,320
Yeah.

444
00:37:03,920 --> 00:37:04,760
What is it?

445
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:06,199
Well,

446
00:37:06,719 --> 00:37:08,679
I'd like to go back to England sooner.

447
00:37:10,199 --> 00:37:12,679
I thought I'd go back this weekend.

448
00:37:13,280 --> 00:37:15,320
What happened? Didn't you want to stay?

449
00:37:15,960 --> 00:37:19,079
While your dad's away,
you should pretend you're flying back.

450
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:24,960
Well… I want to get back
to continue my project.

451
00:37:25,039 --> 00:37:27,880
I feel like I can't focus while I'm here.

452
00:37:30,280 --> 00:37:31,880
Then you can run away with me.

453
00:37:33,079 --> 00:37:34,719
I'll take you to a clinic.

454
00:37:34,800 --> 00:37:37,039
When you feel better,
you can fly back to England.

455
00:37:39,400 --> 00:37:40,559
Go ahead.

456
00:37:59,159 --> 00:38:00,840
If you weren't in a hurry,

457
00:38:00,920 --> 00:38:03,079
I'd have flown back with you.

458
00:38:14,840 --> 00:38:17,079
Since you're already here, Auntie Oon,

459
00:38:18,159 --> 00:38:23,039
I'd like you to spend as much time
with your family as possible.

460
00:38:23,719 --> 00:38:25,519
You must have missed each other.

461
00:38:25,599 --> 00:38:29,519
Besides, you'll have to go back to England
and stay with me for a long time.

462
00:38:32,440 --> 00:38:33,880
I spend time with you

463
00:38:33,960 --> 00:38:35,719
not only because it's my duty,

464
00:38:36,239 --> 00:38:39,320
but also because I raised you,
so I love you in my own way.

465
00:38:39,920 --> 00:38:41,079
When someone hurts you,

466
00:38:41,719 --> 00:38:43,079
they hurt me even more.

467
00:38:43,760 --> 00:38:46,480
Don't talk as if you were
a stranger to me.

468
00:38:46,559 --> 00:38:49,199
You're just like one of my own children.

469
00:39:14,840 --> 00:39:16,440
The first step is complete.

470
00:39:19,840 --> 00:39:22,360
You look so happy using your phone.

471
00:39:22,440 --> 00:39:24,760
Either you won the lottery,
or you found a woman.

472
00:39:24,840 --> 00:39:27,000
You're too interested
in other people's lives.

473
00:39:28,360 --> 00:39:31,039
Which rich person
are you getting into bed now?

474
00:39:31,119 --> 00:39:33,480
"If you still can't tell sex from love,

475
00:39:33,559 --> 00:39:36,320
you won't find
true love in this life," Gaogla.

476
00:39:36,400 --> 00:39:38,719
If you're not careful,
you'll go to prison.

477
00:39:39,679 --> 00:39:42,880
-Damn you, Khem.
-Hey, bro, relax.

478
00:39:42,960 --> 00:39:44,639
Hey, relax, bro.

479
00:39:46,920 --> 00:39:47,960
There's that smile.

480
00:39:48,039 --> 00:39:49,280
-Khem!
-Okay, bye.

481
00:39:58,800 --> 00:40:01,199
Please call me when you get there.

482
00:40:03,599 --> 00:40:04,760
Yes, Auntie.

483
00:40:04,840 --> 00:40:06,199
Take her to the check-in desk.

484
00:40:06,280 --> 00:40:07,280
Yes, ma'am.

485
00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:10,239
That's not necessary.

486
00:40:10,320 --> 00:40:12,719
-What? Why?
-Wait. I can do it myself.

487
00:40:13,239 --> 00:40:14,360
-Really?
-Really, Auntie.

488
00:40:14,880 --> 00:40:16,360
My dear.

489
00:40:34,880 --> 00:40:35,800
I have to go.

490
00:40:35,880 --> 00:40:37,559
Remember. Don't forget to call me.

491
00:40:38,159 --> 00:40:39,000
Sure.

492
00:41:25,199 --> 00:41:26,480
What's wrong?

493
00:41:33,599 --> 00:41:34,599
Is this right?

494
00:41:35,960 --> 00:41:37,800
You came this far to hesitate now?

495
00:41:52,159 --> 00:41:53,159
I feel like

496
00:41:54,559 --> 00:41:56,280
I'm betraying my family.

497
00:41:59,280 --> 00:42:01,800
I'm a brat just like my dad said I was.

498
00:42:07,519 --> 00:42:08,800
If you turn back now,

499
00:42:09,320 --> 00:42:10,559
will everything get better?

500
00:42:35,239 --> 00:42:36,880
We've all made mistakes.

501
00:42:39,280 --> 00:42:40,639
And when we behave badly,

502
00:42:41,679 --> 00:42:43,719
we really want our parents
to understand us.

503
00:42:44,239 --> 00:42:45,920
But each of our mistakes

504
00:42:46,800 --> 00:42:48,519
could make us impossible to love.

505
00:42:49,760 --> 00:42:51,519
So we can't let them know what we did

506
00:42:51,599 --> 00:42:53,639
if we still want them to truly love us.

507
00:43:02,440 --> 00:43:05,639
We're not running from our problem.
We're just solving it.

508
00:43:07,280 --> 00:43:09,719
In three days,
you'll be a good girl just like before.

509
00:43:11,239 --> 00:43:13,599
Once it's solved,
we never have to meet again.

510
00:43:15,559 --> 00:43:17,239
Your future is the top priority.

511
00:44:11,360 --> 00:44:12,519
Stay here today.

512
00:44:12,599 --> 00:44:15,360
The garage is busy.
I don't want anyone to know about us.

513
00:44:15,960 --> 00:44:18,360
The clinic will see you tomorrow.
We'll go together.

514
00:44:26,960 --> 00:44:28,239
Are you okay on your own?

515
00:44:28,320 --> 00:44:29,159
Should I stay?

516
00:44:30,960 --> 00:44:31,880
See you tomorrow.

517
00:44:41,000 --> 00:44:42,760
Why are you so scared?

518
00:44:42,840 --> 00:44:45,159
Call me if you need help.
The garage is close by.

519
00:45:06,960 --> 00:45:07,800
Hey, Khem.

520
00:45:08,559 --> 00:45:09,519
What happened?

521
00:45:09,599 --> 00:45:10,840
Someone messed with us.

522
00:45:11,639 --> 00:45:13,440
Maybe it's that showroom owner.

523
00:45:14,079 --> 00:45:15,559
He trashed the place.

524
00:45:15,639 --> 00:45:17,280
He must've been after something.

525
00:45:18,719 --> 00:45:19,639
Is anything missing?

526
00:45:21,840 --> 00:45:22,880
Where are the ECUs?

527
00:45:22,960 --> 00:45:23,880
Hey, don't bother.

528
00:45:24,440 --> 00:45:28,119
Luckily, I thought ahead.
I hid them in your house already.

529
00:45:28,199 --> 00:45:30,280
What? In my house?

530
00:45:30,360 --> 00:45:32,880
Yeah. I'll go and check on them.

531
00:45:32,960 --> 00:45:34,000
Hey, don't worry.

532
00:45:34,719 --> 00:45:35,679
I'll check on them.

533
00:45:36,199 --> 00:45:37,119
You clean up here.

534
00:45:41,679 --> 00:45:42,719
SAIKHIM

535
00:45:44,559 --> 00:45:45,400
What is it?

536
00:45:46,960 --> 00:45:48,280
What?

537
00:45:53,440 --> 00:45:55,159
It was like this when I got here.

538
00:45:55,920 --> 00:45:56,800
Were you burgled?

539
00:46:15,360 --> 00:46:16,320
What are those?

540
00:46:16,400 --> 00:46:17,360
What's in there?

541
00:46:19,119 --> 00:46:20,679
What they wanted to steal.

542
00:46:34,840 --> 00:46:35,679
You troublemaker.

543
00:46:36,199 --> 00:46:41,280
You had the nerve to snitch to the cops
while you took money from my peers and me.

544
00:46:42,039 --> 00:46:44,239
You shouldn't have flown
so close to the sun.

545
00:46:44,760 --> 00:46:46,280
You even ran off with Saikhim.

546
00:46:51,920 --> 00:46:54,239
-What do you mean?
-Saikhim isn't on the plane.

547
00:46:54,760 --> 00:46:56,000
You deceived my cousin.

548
00:46:56,599 --> 00:46:58,280
You thought you'd outsmart me?

549
00:46:58,880 --> 00:47:01,639
You took my cousin
so that you could get rich faster, right?

550
00:47:03,159 --> 00:47:04,159
What do you want?

551
