-You're hungry?

796
01:04:37,679 --> 01:04:38,960
I'll do the best I can.

797
01:04:39,039 --> 01:04:40,480
Hey, tell me what you want.

798
01:04:40,559 --> 01:04:41,760
-You're the best.
-Tell me.

799
01:04:45,119 --> 01:04:47,679
Let's take a shower and brush our teeth.

800
01:04:48,199 --> 01:04:49,119
So having a mom

801
01:04:50,559 --> 01:04:52,000
is nice like this.

802
01:04:53,199 --> 01:04:56,239
When a student has a baby,
they grow up together like this.

803
01:05:04,000 --> 01:05:06,119
She's a former teen mom.

804
01:05:06,719 --> 01:05:09,039
If my mom had been
a deep thinker like you,

805
01:05:09,119 --> 01:05:10,079
I wouldn't be here.

806
01:05:10,159 --> 01:05:13,400
She didn't think hard enough,
so now you're all stuck with me.

807
01:05:41,719 --> 01:05:42,760
My goodness.

808
01:05:42,840 --> 01:05:44,360
I thought you'd flake out.

809
01:05:44,440 --> 01:05:45,400
I'm not holding on.

810
01:05:46,079 --> 01:05:49,480
Hey, did you actually sleep in your car
to watch over Saikhim?

811
01:05:51,480 --> 01:05:52,519
Is Khim awake?

812
01:05:53,559 --> 01:05:54,400
Yeah.

813
01:06:04,239 --> 01:06:05,280
What are you doing?

814
01:06:07,400 --> 01:06:08,519
You took the pill?

815
01:06:09,119 --> 01:06:10,880
Did you? What did you take?

816
01:06:10,960 --> 01:06:11,840
Spit it out.

817
01:06:12,400 --> 01:06:13,599
Come on, spit it out.

818
01:06:51,960 --> 01:06:53,119
What are you doing?

819
01:07:07,440 --> 01:07:08,320
It's candy?

820
01:07:08,400 --> 01:07:09,800
Of course it is.

821
01:07:10,480 --> 01:07:13,840
I didn't know. I thought
you got impatient and took that pill.

822
01:07:14,920 --> 01:07:16,119
I'm sorry.

823
01:07:16,199 --> 01:07:17,199
I didn't mean it.

824
01:07:18,199 --> 01:07:19,480
You didn't mean it?

825
01:07:19,559 --> 01:07:22,239
But you kissed Khim so deeply.

826
01:07:27,360 --> 01:07:29,199
-Khim?
-Khim?

827
01:07:29,280 --> 01:07:30,119
Hey.

828
01:07:30,639 --> 01:07:32,320
Where did that kiss come from?

829
01:07:35,079 --> 01:07:37,159
-Khim. Hey!
-Stop, you psycho!

830
01:07:37,239 --> 01:07:38,159
-Hey!
-Get out!

831
01:07:38,239 --> 01:07:39,159
-Khim!
-Get out!

832
01:07:39,239 --> 01:07:41,239
-My goodness. Do this.
-Mom, it's too short.

833
01:07:41,320 --> 01:07:42,519
-Hey!
-Yeah!

834
01:07:42,599 --> 01:07:43,679
Mom, go all out.

835
01:07:43,760 --> 01:07:44,639
-Get out!
-Yeah!

836
01:07:57,960 --> 01:07:58,800
This is crazy.

837
01:08:00,480 --> 01:08:01,840
How dare he do that?

838
01:08:03,960 --> 01:08:05,119
He should have asked.

839
01:08:28,239 --> 01:08:29,359
What have I done?

840
01:08:30,560 --> 01:08:31,399
Damn it.

841
01:08:46,880 --> 01:08:47,840
For goodness' sake.

842
01:08:48,720 --> 01:08:50,079
How can I face her now?

843
01:08:55,119 --> 01:08:56,319
LITA

844
01:09:03,000 --> 01:09:05,840
Who are you,
and what right have you to invade my home?

845
01:09:05,920 --> 01:09:07,439
Just go away right now.

846
01:09:07,960 --> 01:09:09,279
GAOGLA

847
01:09:09,359 --> 01:09:10,760
I'm looking for Miss Saikhim.

848
01:09:10,840 --> 01:09:12,359
Saikhim?

849
01:09:13,680 --> 01:09:14,880
Why would she be here?

850
01:09:14,960 --> 01:09:16,960
Miss Khim ran away from home yesterday.

851
01:09:17,680 --> 01:09:19,319
May we search your property?

852
01:09:22,720 --> 01:09:23,600
You may not!

853
01:09:23,680 --> 01:09:27,399
We both told you that she's not here,
so you've no right to search here.

854
01:09:27,479 --> 01:09:29,119
Her father's very worried about her.

855
01:09:29,199 --> 01:09:31,159
If there's evidence
that she contacted you,

856
01:09:31,680 --> 01:09:33,760
it could make it easier
for us to find her.

857
01:09:33,840 --> 01:09:36,880
How could the two of us
know where Saikhim went?

858
01:09:37,640 --> 01:09:40,279
If you search our home,

859
01:09:40,359 --> 01:09:43,840
and you damage our possessions,
you have to take care of the damages.

860
01:09:55,479 --> 01:09:56,439
Where is Saikhim?

861
01:09:58,159 --> 01:09:59,199
How should I know?

862
01:09:59,279 --> 01:10:01,359
I know you took her away with you.

863
01:10:01,960 --> 01:10:03,880
Can you afford to keep her happy?

864
01:10:03,960 --> 01:10:05,760
Is that why you took her from me?

865
01:10:06,479 --> 01:10:07,520
Let me ask you this.

866
01:10:08,119 --> 01:10:10,920
If you made her so happy,
why would she run from you?

867
01:10:11,640 --> 01:10:13,479
Leave my daughter alone.

868
01:10:14,880 --> 01:10:16,800
Don't use this baby to manipulate her.

869
01:10:16,880 --> 01:10:19,199
You can't even survive on your own.

870
01:10:19,279 --> 01:10:21,199
How can you look after a woman?

871
01:10:23,119 --> 01:10:25,319
I admit that I don't have
the resources you do.

872
01:10:25,399 --> 01:10:27,720
Although I can't afford a gilded cage,

873
01:10:28,359 --> 01:10:29,760
I can give her the sky.

874
01:10:29,840 --> 01:10:31,399
You should think about it.

875
01:10:31,920 --> 01:10:35,600
Between a gilded cage and the sky,
which would a bird rather have?

876
01:10:35,680 --> 01:10:38,600
Even if I had nothing but my body,
you still couldn't beat me

877
01:10:38,680 --> 01:10:40,680
because you never let her be free,

878
01:10:40,760 --> 01:10:42,680
so she flies back to me, the scumbag.

879
01:10:55,600 --> 01:10:58,159
Call the cops, honey. Call them.

880
01:10:59,000 --> 01:11:00,359
Hey!

881
01:11:00,439 --> 01:11:02,399
-Hey!
-You can't go up there, sir!

882
01:11:02,479 --> 01:11:03,399
Don't go there.

883
01:11:04,199 --> 01:11:05,520
-No one's there.
-Get out now!

884
01:11:05,600 --> 01:11:06,720
You can't go up there.

885
01:11:06,800 --> 01:11:08,640
You can't go there without permission.

886
01:11:08,720 --> 01:11:12,640
That's so rude. It's my home.
I told you you can't do this!

887
01:11:13,319 --> 01:11:14,159
Don't open it!

888
01:11:36,600 --> 01:11:38,439
You're not allowed to open it!

889
01:11:41,039 --> 01:11:42,520
-Don't open it, sir!
-Don't!

890
01:11:49,600 --> 01:11:51,000
Close it now.

891
01:11:56,119 --> 01:11:59,399
See? There's nothing there.
Only panties hung out to dry. Your loss.

892
01:11:59,479 --> 01:12:00,560
-Satisfied?
-Yeah.

893
01:12:00,640 --> 01:12:02,359
-We said there was nothing.
-Yeah.

894
01:12:08,520 --> 01:12:12,039
-Hey, we said there was nothing up there!
-We said there was nothing there!

895
01:12:16,439 --> 01:12:18,399
-Mr. Sansern!
-There's nothing up there.

896
01:12:18,479 --> 01:12:19,359
Don't go inside.

897
01:12:19,439 --> 01:12:21,680
It's our home.
You don't have our permission.

898
01:12:22,319 --> 01:12:24,319
How dare you? Who do you think you are?

899
01:12:24,399 --> 01:12:26,159
How dare you disrespect the law?

900
01:12:33,319 --> 01:12:36,520
If Miss Saikhim isn't here,
you don't need to worry.

901
01:12:37,399 --> 01:12:40,239
If you really are her friends,
you should cooperate

902
01:12:40,319 --> 01:12:42,000
so I can find her sooner.

903
01:12:43,880 --> 01:12:45,279
Such a rude attitude.

904
01:12:45,359 --> 01:12:48,479
No wonder she can't stand you.
It's good that she ran away.

905
01:12:49,960 --> 01:12:50,800
Mr. Sansern!

906
01:13:06,359 --> 01:13:07,199
Gaogla.

907
01:13:12,239 --> 01:13:13,479
Get back inside!

908
01:13:15,880 --> 01:13:17,199
Someone's there.

909
01:13:17,279 --> 01:13:18,640
Stay still!

910
01:13:27,079 --> 01:13:28,479
See? There's nothing there.

911
01:13:34,359 --> 01:13:35,439
Mr. Sansern.

912
01:13:47,600 --> 01:13:49,800
We told you there was nothing there.

913
01:13:52,279 --> 01:13:53,760
See? For goodness' sake.

914
01:13:53,840 --> 01:13:57,119
So much walking around for nothing.
We told you there was nothing.

915
01:14:03,479 --> 01:14:05,680
-There's nothing there.
-They're still searching.

916
01:14:05,760 --> 01:14:08,279
-You searched already.
-We said there was nothing!

917
01:14:08,359 --> 01:14:10,279
-You searched there already.
-Yeah.

918
01:14:11,359 --> 01:14:12,520
Stay still, okay?

919
01:14:18,159 --> 01:14:19,119
Hand me the bag.

920
01:14:38,000 --> 01:14:41,159
We said there was nothing.
Why won't you believe us? Damn.

921
01:14:44,119 --> 01:14:45,520
Has Gaogla been in contact?

922
01:14:45,600 --> 01:14:46,520
Gaogla?

923
01:14:47,520 --> 01:14:48,479
Who's that?

924
01:14:48,560 --> 01:14:50,840
He tricked Miss Khim into running away.

925
01:14:51,840 --> 01:14:53,319
This is the second time.

926
01:14:57,439 --> 01:15:01,399
So you know they ran off together.
But why are you searching here?

927
01:15:01,479 --> 01:15:03,159
Your daughter may have helped them.

928
01:15:04,600 --> 01:15:06,159
Such strange ideas

929
01:15:06,239 --> 01:15:07,920
tend to come from your daughter.

930
01:15:09,119 --> 01:15:09,960
Really?

931
01:15:12,359 --> 01:15:15,439
But I really have no idea this time, Mom.

932
01:15:18,399 --> 01:15:19,359
I swear.

933
01:15:23,800 --> 01:15:25,560
Stay calm. Don't be afraid.

934
01:15:26,640 --> 01:15:27,800
Carefully take a step.

935
01:15:30,159 --> 01:15:31,520
Give me your hand.

936
01:15:37,760 --> 01:15:38,960
Look over here.

937
01:15:45,600 --> 01:15:46,560
Move slowly.

938
01:15:49,319 --> 01:15:51,199
Count to three, then take a step.

939
01:15:53,960 --> 01:15:56,680
One. Two. Three.

940
01:16:09,119 --> 01:16:10,760
We're done. There's nothing there.

941
01:16:14,479 --> 01:16:15,640
-Told you.
-Unbelievable.

942
01:16:15,720 --> 01:16:16,760
And these clothes?

943
01:16:18,199 --> 01:16:19,279
We didn't find those.

944
01:16:22,239 --> 01:16:24,239
Mom, we've had no clients yet today.

945
01:16:24,319 --> 01:16:26,119
That's awful. In that case,

946
01:16:26,199 --> 01:16:29,600
since you kept my clients away,
why don't you try a facial massage?

947
01:16:29,680 --> 01:16:31,640
-Would you like a facial massage?
-No.

948
01:16:31,720 --> 01:16:34,520
-Where are my clients? Take this.
-That's enough.

949
01:16:34,600 --> 01:16:36,520
-Take this.
-Hey. Wait.

950
01:16:36,600 --> 01:16:37,439
That's enough.

951
01:16:42,680 --> 01:16:45,800
Here you go.
Compensation for reduced foot traffic.

952
01:16:46,319 --> 01:16:48,239
If you hear of those two, call me.

953
01:16:48,840 --> 01:16:49,680
That's all?

954
01:16:49,760 --> 01:16:50,600
You don't want it?

955
01:16:51,479 --> 01:16:54,520
Hey, wait. I'll take it. Jeez.

956
01:16:55,079 --> 01:16:57,920
All right, who wants a facial massage?

957
01:16:58,000 --> 01:17:01,039
Another facial massage?
Yes? Facial massage?

958
01:17:01,119 --> 01:17:02,399
Thanks for your business.

959
01:17:05,720 --> 01:17:06,640
That was close.

960
01:17:10,079 --> 01:17:10,920
Gently.

961
01:17:11,640 --> 01:17:12,479
Are you okay?

962
01:17:16,279 --> 01:17:19,399
If you want to trust me with your life,
we must trust each other.

963
01:17:19,920 --> 01:17:21,159
Then we'll both survive.

964
01:17:26,760 --> 01:17:27,760
All three of us.

965
01:17:45,920 --> 01:17:47,039
It'll survive, right?

966
01:17:49,359 --> 01:17:50,319
That's up to you

967
01:17:51,279 --> 01:17:52,600
whether it stays or goes.

968
01:17:53,760 --> 01:17:56,239
But with me, it will be safe.

969
01:17:58,119 --> 01:17:59,079
Are you sure?

970
01:17:59,159 --> 01:18:00,039
Of course.

971
01:18:02,840 --> 01:18:05,720
I got killed at sea, but I'm still alive.

972
01:18:07,159 --> 01:18:09,119
-Come on.
-Don't be silly.

973
01:18:10,560 --> 01:18:13,640
Actually, I'm helping you
avoid getting arrested.

974
01:18:24,439 --> 01:18:27,159
If I'd died that day,
where would you be today?

975
01:18:30,079 --> 01:18:31,479
Well, I guess

976
01:18:32,680 --> 01:18:34,279
I'd be hanging over there,

977
01:18:34,800 --> 01:18:35,640
or maybe

978
01:18:36,760 --> 01:18:37,920
lying still down there.

979
01:18:40,640 --> 01:18:42,479
If all three of us survive,

980
01:18:43,920 --> 01:18:45,279
can I ask you something?

981
01:18:46,920 --> 01:18:47,760
What is it?

982
01:18:50,119 --> 01:18:50,960
I'd ilke…

983
01:18:52,359 --> 01:18:53,680
Hey!

984
01:18:58,560 --> 01:18:59,399
Hey!

985
01:19:03,039 --> 01:19:04,000
Are you okay?

986
01:19:07,840 --> 01:19:08,760
Is it okay?

987
01:19:14,760 --> 01:19:15,960
Watch out!

988
01:19:23,920 --> 01:19:27,279
The doctor says the X-ray results are in,
and the patient is safe.

989
01:19:27,359 --> 01:19:29,760
There are only cuts and bruises.

990
01:19:29,840 --> 01:19:32,119
We'll treat the wounds,
then he can go home.

991
01:19:32,199 --> 01:19:33,039
Thank you.

992
01:19:48,520 --> 01:19:49,560
Since we met,

993
01:19:50,880 --> 01:19:52,479
I've gotten you hurt so many times.

994
01:19:53,479 --> 01:19:54,880
I've ruined your life too.

995
01:19:55,720 --> 01:19:57,760
Your dad must know about the baby by now.

996
01:20:01,359 --> 01:20:04,159
It's time to go to the clinic.
We should go now.

997
01:20:06,680 --> 01:20:08,119
It managed to survive.

998
01:20:10,520 --> 01:20:11,720
We can't kill it now.

999
01:20:18,239 --> 01:20:20,960
It's not just the baby's life.
Your life is important too.

1000
01:20:21,479 --> 01:20:25,680
I'm worried about your future too.
As for me, I have nothing to lose.

1001
01:20:28,119 --> 01:20:29,399
Just before our accident,

1002
01:20:30,600 --> 01:20:33,319
you wanted to ask me something.

1003
01:20:36,720 --> 01:20:38,079
If all three of us survive,

1004
01:20:38,600 --> 01:20:39,840
can I ask you something?

1005
01:20:41,520 --> 01:20:42,359
What is it?

1006
01:20:47,279 --> 01:20:48,560
What did you want to ask?

1007
01:20:50,000 --> 01:20:52,279
How can I repay you?

1008
01:20:57,119 --> 01:20:59,039
I'd like you to give me sole custody.

1009
01:21:01,000 --> 01:21:02,159
I can handle one kid.

1010
01:21:07,239 --> 01:21:08,640
But I know it's impossible.

1011
01:21:09,600 --> 01:21:11,720
Ruining your life to have the baby

1012
01:21:13,359 --> 01:21:14,359
is too much to ask.

1013
01:21:16,640 --> 01:21:17,880
Eight or nine months

1014
01:21:18,800 --> 01:21:20,399
aren't worth the sacrifice, right?

1015
01:21:55,680 --> 01:21:57,199
But with me, it will be safe.

1016
01:21:59,439 --> 01:22:00,359
Is it okay?

1017
01:22:01,079 --> 01:22:02,199
Watch out!

1018
01:22:37,840 --> 01:22:38,800
Come on.

1019
01:22:44,000 --> 01:22:44,840
Wait.

1020
01:22:51,720 --> 01:22:55,000
Could you… show me…

1021
01:22:57,000 --> 01:22:58,720
how you'll raise it?

1022
01:23:01,479 --> 01:23:02,960
If you can cope with raising it,

1023
01:23:03,840 --> 01:23:05,239
I'll give you sole custody.

1024
01:23:08,760 --> 01:23:10,800
Are you sure you'll keep the baby?

1025
01:23:11,560 --> 01:23:14,039
Honestly, I think this guy is useless.

1026
01:23:14,560 --> 01:23:17,279
Shouldn't we regroup here
and figure it out together?

1027
01:23:21,119 --> 01:23:26,079
Thanks for caring about me, Lita.
But I can take care of myself.

1028
01:23:27,399 --> 01:23:28,239
Khim.

1029
01:23:28,920 --> 01:23:30,680
Your life isn't over yet.

1030
01:23:31,199 --> 01:23:35,279
Come back, and we'll figure it out.
We might find a better solution.

1031
01:23:37,439 --> 01:23:39,840
We can't go back and fix things anyway.

1032
01:23:40,439 --> 01:23:44,000
I'd rather move forward
even if there's an abyss in front of me.

1033
01:24:41,079 --> 01:24:42,800
I never thought a rich kid like her

1034
01:24:43,319 --> 01:24:45,960
would agree to try her luck
with me when I've no future.

1035
01:24:46,800 --> 01:24:49,479
No matter how smart you are,
anyone can make mistakes.

1036
01:24:50,800 --> 01:24:53,479
I admit that I messed up
because of something stupid.

1037
01:26:34,680 --> 01:26:36,640
You asked me how I would raise the kid.

1038
01:26:37,560 --> 01:26:38,399
This is how.

1039
01:26:39,000 --> 01:26:40,720
I'll raise it where I grew up.

1040
01:26:47,560 --> 01:26:49,760
Don't worry. It won't turn out like me.

1041
01:26:53,680 --> 01:26:55,640
I promise, I can take good care of it.

1042
01:26:56,520 --> 01:26:59,479
I'll show the kid
how lucky we all are to be alive.

1043
01:26:59,560 --> 01:27:01,520
At least it will have an awesome life.

1044
01:27:02,399 --> 01:27:04,279
It will be a life worth living.

1045
01:27:11,720 --> 01:27:13,800
And it won't starve
like when it's with you.

1046
01:27:17,840 --> 01:27:20,800
No. Actually, I'm not that hungry.

1047
01:27:22,520 --> 01:27:23,600
Stop acting tough.

1048
01:27:24,399 --> 01:27:26,479
We've come too far to be embarrassed now.

1049
01:27:34,439 --> 01:27:36,159
You act like we're strangers.

1050
01:27:38,880 --> 01:27:40,800
Since when have we been close friends?

1051
01:27:42,640 --> 01:27:43,720
You're so closed off.

1052
01:27:45,800 --> 01:27:46,920
We're distant friends.

1053
01:27:48,760 --> 01:27:49,960
Am I distant enough now?

1054
01:27:50,520 --> 01:27:51,720
Distant enough for you?

1055
01:27:52,520 --> 01:27:53,359
How about now?

1056
01:27:55,520 --> 01:27:58,279
Because of her,
I want to be a good person again.

1057
01:28:18,239 --> 01:28:20,680
I think Gaogla is using that kid
to manipulate Khim

1058
01:28:20,760 --> 01:28:22,159
to defy us, actually, Uncle.

1059
01:28:22,239 --> 01:28:23,199
Did you abduct her?

1060
01:28:23,279 --> 01:28:24,680
Who do you think I am, Dad?

1061
01:28:24,760 --> 01:28:26,359
You're hotheaded and impatient.

1062
01:28:26,880 --> 01:28:29,239
You good-for-nothing.
What have you ever done right?

1063
01:28:29,319 --> 01:28:31,079
-What are you doing here?
-Dad, enough.

1064
01:28:31,159 --> 01:28:32,159
-Dad!
-You…

1065
01:28:32,760 --> 01:28:34,000
What are you doing here?

1066
01:28:34,079 --> 01:28:36,720
You see what happens
when you let emotions run your life?

1067
01:28:38,279 --> 01:28:39,399
So what do you think?

1068
01:28:40,199 --> 01:28:41,680
Would you live here with me?

1069
01:28:42,439 --> 01:28:44,079
Who would I be to you here?

1070
01:28:44,159 --> 01:28:45,279
Why are you so scared?

1071
01:28:48,479 --> 01:28:49,359
Don't.

1072
01:28:49,439 --> 01:28:52,720
I'll take responsibility
for the damage to your daughter's life.

1073
01:28:52,800 --> 01:28:53,840
If you don't mind,

1074
01:28:54,680 --> 01:28:56,039
my son wants to marry Saikhim.

1075
01:28:56,760 --> 01:28:58,159
Gla!

1076
